wikipedia_page.main: Julie Anne Paulding née Forrester (born 4 May 1969, Prenton, Birkenhead) is an English competitive track cyclist who won silver in the 500m Time Trial at the 2002 Commonwealth Games in Manchester. She had taken up cycling four years previously having been forced to give up her previous sport due to injury.Paulding is now a development officer for Scottish Cycling. She lives in Manchester and married Steve Paulding in October 2001.
